#
# The purpose of this project is to make it insanely easy to start up a 
# python3.4 + django1.7 project. It uses Vagrant to do so.
#
# Prerequisites:
#  	1) 	 Vagrant 	- https://www.vagrantup.com/downloads.html
# 	2) 	 Git 		
#
# Step 1:
# 	1.	 git clone https://GITUSERNAME@bitbucket.org/GITUSERNAME/vagrant-django.git
# 	2.	 cd vagrant-django
#	3. 	 vagrant up
# 	4. 	 vagrant ssh
#   
# 		To connect from a browser on your local computer, bring up gunicorn or runserver:
#
# 	5a.   cd /vagrant && ./manage.py runserver 127.0.0.1:8000
#       or
#   5b.   cd /vagrant && /home/vagrant/venv/bin/gunicorn mysite.wsgi	 
